Introduction

Han Seung Yeon, or Seungyeon, is a Korean singer and actress known for being the main vocalist of the girl group, KARA, under DSP Media which debuted on March 29, 2007.

On January 26, 2015, it was announced that Seungyeon signed a contract with J,Wide Company

On January 14, 2016, Seungyeon's contract with DSP Media was terminated & the following day, KARA was disbanded. Following this, she pursued a career in acting. One of her most memorable roles was as Jung Ye-Eun in the drama Age of Youth (also known as Hello, My Twenties!).

On March 1, 2018, it was announced that Seungyeon's exclusive contract with J,Wide had been terminated & 12 days later, on March 13th, she signed a contract with Inyeon Entertainment. Then, on April 1, 2020, it was announced that her contract had been terminated and, 13 days later, on April 14, 2020, Seungyeon signed a contract with YG Entertainment's subsidiary label, YGX Entertainment.
